Key Match Events: Jayson Tatum made the deciding 3-pointer at the overtime buzzer to give the Boston Celtics a 126-123 victory over the Toronto Raptors.
The NBA revealed that Jayson Tatum traveled moments before making the deciding 3-pointer, and Davion Mitchell should have been called for a foul against Jaylen Brown with 7 seconds remaining.
Others: The NBA publicly releases reports of officiated events — calls and notable non-calls — when games were at or within three points at any time in the last two minutes of the fourth quarter or overtime.
